sp_scores.title: Attack Titan (Earth King) with a wind attack.

tip_battle.html_content:
Titan
Poison / Silence / Paralyze / Confuse / Slow / Stop / Reflect / Blind / Sleep / Petrify / Doom / Instant KO / Berserk / Sap / Interrupt
Earthen Wall
Poison / Silence / Paralyze / Confuse / Slow / Stop / Reflect / Blind / Sleep / Petrify / Doom / Instant KO / Berserk / Sap / Interrupt
tip_battle.title: Titan (Earth King)
tip_battle.message:
• -The enemy has resistance to all damage, and physical attacks also deal reduced damage.
  • -While infused with the power of wind, the wind damage you deal to the enemy increases, and the damage you take from certain enemy attacks is reduced.
  • -The enemy targets heroes that draw attention to themselves with Rock Assault, which Interrupts, ignoring resistances.
  • -After losing a certain amount of HP, the enemy forms an earthen wall that reduces damage under 50,000 to zero, and prevents attacks from hitting Titan until the wall is destroyed.
  • -The enemy uses Wind Diffusion to weaken infusion with the power of wind.
  • -The enemy uses Primal Essence, which deals all types of elemental damage.
  • -If the fight lasts too long and you haven't reduced the enemy's HP enough, it uses Creation Gaia's Wrath, which will KO the entire party.
  • -Once a certain number of turns pass, or after the enemy loses a certain amount of HP, its Rage level increases (up to level 3).
  • -The higher the enemy's Rage level, the less damage you'll be able to deal to it.
  • -Deal damage greater than the damage cap to lower the Rage level by 1.

tip_battle.title: Hecatoncheir (Savage)
tip_battle.message:
• -Magic and ninjutsu attacks deal reduced damage.
  • -Uses strong earth attacks.
  • -Uses resistance-ignoring attacks that can Blind and Confuse.
  • -Uses Looming Wrath to attack with a reduced delay.
  • -Uses Savage Looming Wrath to increase its Attack and Defense, and attack with a reduced delay.
  • -Uses Savage Gaian Salvo to briefly lower the Attack and Magic of those hit, ignoring Mirror Image and Defense.
  • -Uses Savage Quake, which removes Haste.
  • -When it uses Earth Rage to Enrage, its speed greatly increases, but the amount of damage it deals decreases.
  • -You can remove Earth Rage by dealing damage greater than the damage cap.

sp_scores.title: Attack Adamantoise with a wind attack.

tip_battle.html_content:
Adamantoise
Poison / Silence / Paralyze / Confuse / Slow / Stop / Reflect / Blind / Sleep / Petrify / Doom / Instant KO / Berserk / Sap / Interrupt
tip_battle.title: Adamantoise (Savage)
tip_battle.message:
• -Physical attacks deal reduced damage.
  • -Uses strong earth attacks.
  • -Restores HP using Heal.
  • -Uses Confounding Roar, which inflicts Confuse and ignores resistances.
  • -Uses Adamant Guard to grant itself Protect and Shell.
  • -Uses Savage Adamant Guard to grant itself Protect and Shell, and raise its Defense, Resistance, and Mind for a short period of time.
  • -Uses Savage Gaia's Fury, which Interrupts Actions, ignoring resistances, and ignores Mirror Image and Defense.
  • -Uses Savage Bestial Resonance, which ignores Resistance and removes Haste.
  • -When it uses Earth Rage to Enrage, the amount of damage it takes is greatly lowered, but its actions get slower.
  • -You can remove Earth Rage by dealing damage greater than the damage cap.
